Well this is what I always do:

Lets say I edit client.java. I’m gonna save the file but not close it. So if I made some mistakes I can undo them. That way if I get a problem, I just undo.

By the way… You should use Notepad++, because you can do undo like unlimited times and I’m not about normal notepad.
